00:00:42.660 --> 00:00:47.840
The chip is for high, soft floated passes.
Kicking for distance and height will be a

00:00:47.840 --> 00:00:52.480
similar technique. If you can do the chip
with confidence, it will make kicking high

00:00:52.480 --> 00:00:54.070
and far easier.

00:00:54.070 --> 00:01:01.070
Key Point #1 - Line up behind the ball and
a tad to the side.

00:01:03.250 --> 00:01:09.790
Key Point #2 - Your shoulders should face
your target on your approach and follow through.

00:01:09.790 --> 00:01:14.320
Turn your shoulders and the ball will go where
your shoulders told it to. Think of your shoulders

00:01:14.320 --> 00:01:19.000
like the scope of a gun. If the scope is off
you aint hitting your target son!

00:01:19.000 --> 00:01:24.290
Key Point #3 - Your plant foot should be 1.5
to 2 steps away from the ball when you make

00:01:24.290 --> 00:01:28.870
contact. This allows your foot to be formatted
properly for your swing.

00:01:28.870 --> 00:01:35.870
Key Point #4 - Turn your kicking foot to the
side, rotate your foot down and make contact

00:01:41.140 --> 00:01:48.140
with the ball just below the base of your
big toe.

00:01:53.190 --> 00:02:00.190
Key Point #5 - Strike the lower part of the
ball but not directly under it. For a chip

00:02:04.720 --> 00:02:09.460
you strike underneath the ball. Doing this
will get your plenty of height but not as

00:02:09.460 --> 00:02:14.320
much distance. By striking on the lower part
of the ball you will still get height but

00:02:14.320 --> 00:02:16.399
a lot more distance.

00:02:16.399 --> 00:02:21.300
Key Point #6 - Have a low back swing and a
low follow through.

00:02:21.300 --> 00:02:26.089
A lot of players look like this when they
make this type of swing. By coming down on

00:02:26.089 --> 00:02:31.190
the ball all that power you created in your
backswing is going down in the ground. You

00:02:31.190 --> 00:02:32.350
don't want that.

00:02:32.350 --> 00:02:37.850
With a low back swing, now all your power
is moving forward in the direction where you

00:02:37.850 --> 00:02:40.279
want the ball to go.

00:02:40.279 --> 00:02:45.109
If you follow through high on your swing this
will cause the ball to not go up as high as

00:02:45.109 --> 00:02:47.109
it should when you kick it.

00:02:47.109 --> 00:02:49.499
You want a low follow through.

00:02:49.499 --> 00:02:56.499
Key Point #7 - It's about technique, not power.
Don't be all Hulk like on your swing!

00:03:00.330 --> 00:03:05.490
You should be smooth. The best players make
this look easy because they relay on technique

00:03:05.490 --> 00:03:07.429
not pure strength.

00:03:07.429 --> 00:03:13.199
Key Point #8 - Make sure you lean back when
you follow through. Do not be hunched over

00:03:13.199 --> 00:03:18.770
the ball.

